    "reasoning": "The Firestore data structure is designed to manage entities for the AgriCentral application. It focuses on clarity, security, and scalability. Authorization Independence is achieved through path-based ownership for user-specific data and membership maps for collaborative data, eliminating the need for `get()` calls in security rules. Structural Segregation ensures that each collection has a homogeneous security posture.  For example, Customers, Suppliers, Workers, and Items are stored in top-level collections. Relationships between entities are managed through document references, as seen in the `customerId` field in the `incomes` and `transactions` collections, and `supplierId` in the `items` collection. This direct reference approach simplifies queries and maintains data integrity. To facilitate real-time data fetching from APIs, consider a server-side function triggered by Firestore writes to update an external cache or trigger downstream API calls based on the changes. This provides real-time updates and can be scaled with the application needs."
